{
  "stem": "15721.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I, I still remember the-- that the bathtub was filled with water to accommodate fish that were kept alive until the cook, on Friday afternoon prepared for the meal.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Oh, there must have been 50, 60 people for, for dinner at our-- I remembered it so well because my parents gave up their bedroom.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The Furniture was totally taken out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And temporary dining tables were set up so that the whole family could eat together in one room.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it, it was really made festive for the-- somewhere, I have a photograph of, of that moment.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And of course, when occasionally I look at it and realize that with the exception of my two brothers, everyone on the photo is, to the best of my knowledge, gone by now.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then, you know, it brings back roots and memories that are very precious.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There had been some talk.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My-- in my mother's family, there was a tradition-- whether it is true or not, I don't know-- that there had been rabbis in the past in Ukraine and, and Eastern Europe.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I knew that my grandfather on my father's side, whom I also didn't know he was dead before I was born, had been a Melamed, a Hebrew teacher.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so there was a, a natural bend in that direction.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then, I must say to you, that my becoming a bar mitzvah was really a decisive moment in my life.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And especially in retrospect, it was possibly what you might call a defining moment.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I decided then that that's what I wanted to be.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There were, during my growing up, my teenage years, a couple of times when I wavered.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I always came back to it and pursued it.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
